1. Header & Footer
header, footer {
  background-color: #ffa500;
  text-align: center;
  min-width: 500px;
}


✅ Good:

Consistent branding with the orange color.

Centered content is visually appealing.

⚠️ Improvements:

Use padding instead of relying solely on image size for spacing:

header, footer {
  padding: 20px 0;
}


Consider flexbox for the header if you want logo + nav later:

header {
  display: flex;
  justify-content: center;
  align-items: center;
}

2. Main Grid Layout
main {
  display: grid;
  grid-template-columns: 250px 250px;
  grid-template-rows: repeat(3, 450px);
  gap: 20px;
  margin-top: 44px;
  grid-auto-rows: 500px;
}


✅ Good:

Two-column grid with gaps is clean.

Each recipe card has a consistent height.

⚠️ Improvements:

Responsive design: On smaller screens, two columns may overflow. Use auto-fit and minmax:

main {
  display: grid;
  grid-template-columns: repeat(auto-fit, minmax(250px, 1fr));
  gap: 20px;
  margin-top: 44px;
}


Remove grid-template-rows and grid-auto-rows, unless you want strict height control. Let content dictate height.

3. Recipe Cards
.recipe {
  box-shadow: 0 1px 1px rgba(0,0,0,0.5);
}


✅ Good:

Subtle shadow adds depth.

⚠️ Improvements:

Add padding & border-radius for better spacing and rounded corners:

.recipe {
  box-shadow: 0 2px 5px rgba(0,0,0,0.3);
  border-radius: 8px;
  overflow: hidden;
  background-color: #fff;
}
.recipe img {
  width: 100%;
  height: auto;
  display: block;
}


Add consistent spacing between <h2>, .time, .mins, and .description:

.recipe h2 {
  margin: 10px;
}
.recipe .time {
  margin-left: 10px;
  vertical-align: middle;
}
.recipe .mins {
  margin-left: 5px;
}
.recipe .description {
  margin: 10px;
  border-top: 1px solid #4a4a4a;
  padding-top: 10px;
}

4. Typography
h2 {
  font-family: Poppins;
  font-size: 18px;
  font-weight: 600;
  letter-spacing: 0.3px;
  text-align: left;
  color: #ffa500;
  padding: 10px 0px 10px 10px;
}
.description {
  font-family: Work Sans;
  font-size: 14px;
  font-weight: 300;
  line-height: 1.29;
  color: #4a4a4a;
}


✅ Good:

Different fonts for headings vs. descriptions.

Color scheme matches branding.

⚠️ Improvements:

Increase line-height for better readability:

.description {
  line-height: 1.5;
}


Use rem instead of px for scalable text:

h2 { font-size: 1.125rem; }
.description { font-size: 0.875rem; }

5. Images & Logos
.logo {
  width: 115px;
  height: 21.1px;
  object-fit: contain;
  padding: 20px;
}


✅ Good:

Fixed logo size ensures consistency.

⚠️ Improvement:

Consider max-width: 100% for responsiveness:

.logo {
  max-width: 115px;
  height: auto;
  padding: 20px;
}


Ensure recipe images have alt text for accessibility.

6. Container
.container {
  min-width: 500px;
  margin: auto;
}


⚠️ Improvement:

Instead of a fixed min-width, use responsive padding:

.container {
  max-width: 600px;
  margin: 0 auto;
  padding: 0 10px;
}


✅ Optional Enhancements

Add hover effect on recipe cards:

.recipe:hover {
  transform: translateY(-5px);
  transition: transform 0.3s;
}


Make time icon and minutes inline:

.time, .mins {
  display: inline-block;
  vertical-align: middle;
}
